# VOICE-GIS

VOICE-GIS is a voice-enabled geospatial mapping web application that allows users to interact with maps using voice commands. The project integrates speech recognition with GIS libraries like Leaflet/OpenLayers for an intuitive user experience.

## 🚀 Features

- 🎤 **Voice Commands**: Zoom in/out, move to specific locations
- 🗺️ **Map Integration**: Uses Leaflet/OpenLayers for map rendering
- 🔥 **Real-time Updates**: Interactive and responsive interface
- 🏎️ **Optimized Performance**: Efficient map rendering with GPU/CPU optimizations

## 📂 Project Structure

```
VOICE-GIS/
│── public/               # Static assets (HTML, images, manifest)
│── src/                  # Source code
│   │── App.js            # Main React Component
│   │── MapComponent.js   # Leaflet/OpenLayers integration
│   │── index.js          # Entry point
│   │── styles/           # CSS styles
│── .gitignore            # Ignore unnecessary files
│── package.json          # Project dependencies
│── README.md             # Project documentation
```

## 🛠️ Installation & Setup

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/voice-gis.git
cd voice-gis
```

### 2️⃣ Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3️⃣ Start Development Server

```bash
npm start
```

👉 The application will run at **[http://localhost:3000/](http://localhost:3000/)**

## 🎤 Voice Commands

- **"Zoom in"** - Increase zoom level
- **"Zoom out"** - Decrease zoom level
- **"Move to Delhi"** - Move map to Delhi
- **"Move to Mumbai"** - Move map to Mumbai
- **"Move to Ahmedabad"** - Move map to Ahmedabad
- **"Move to VIT-AP"** - Move map to VIT-AP Campus

## 🔧 Technologies Used

- **React.js** - Frontend framework
- **Leaflet.js** - GIS & map rendering
- **Web Speech API** - Speech recognition
- **CSS** - Styling

